    <body>
        <p>You can set anchors on many objects that you add to<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic"> a frame</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture"> an image</MadCap:conditionalText>. An anchor is a way to "lock" the position of the object so that it stays in place even if the configuration of the<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic"> frame</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture"> image</MadCap:conditionalText> is changed (e.g., cropped or resized). You can set anchors on any of the four sides of an object—top, bottom, left, right.</p>
